#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:122
msgid ""
"The in-camera autofocus may be fast enough to focus, but it will fail in the "
"most important moment. It is useful for getting the initial focus point, but "
"while shooting it should stay switched off."
